rComments: I loved the layout of her lectures - easy to follow and also visually appealing. She also asks great questions for participation opportunities. As this was a history course, there was a lot of reading and writing, but what you read and write about is interesting, it wasn't too bad. I would take this course again!

All readings are online has a participation aspect for grade but not just in class participation but if talk or email or participate in discussion board feedback on assignments not bad liked my thesis on my proposal but not in my essay even though it was exactly the same
Good grader, enjoyable class, provides good feedback, records lectures and then posts them to blackboard which can help if you miss a class and want to listen to the lecture again.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Participation matters']

rComments: I always thought that profs never actually cared about students issues until I had this prof! I didn't submit an essay because I was actually going through so much with a whole bunch of other assignments and lots of other things outside of school. She emailed me way after the deadline and asked why I didn't and she gave me another chance! Miracle!

Unless you have to I would not recommend taking this class or this professor. She is an extremely hard marker. While she is knowledgeable and I did enjoy what she had to say, I would not take her classes again.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: My favourite prof. during my university career thus far.  Took Women's History.  Clear, interactive, fun, interesting.  Very understanding.  Office hours were helpful.  Always willing to go the extra step to help.  Tutorials were great .  Readings weren't absolutely ESSENTIAL, but they were INCREDIBLY helpful during lectures and for exam. LOVE HER!

Took this class in the summer, the prof was really nice and understanding. I would have done better if I had participated more online or in class. Her material is easy and she's really helpful if you have any questions.
I would take a course with her again. She's quite funny and easy to talk too.
